SIMPLE: reflective
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reflective
<hw>Re*flect"ive</hw> <pr>(r?*fl?kt"?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧flectif</ets>. Cf. <er>Reflexive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Throwing back images; <as>as, a <ex>reflective</ex>
mirror</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the <qex>reflective</qex> stream the sighing bride, viewing her
charms.</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of exercising thought or judgment; <as>as,
<ex>reflective</ex> reason</as>.</def> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His perceptive and <qex>reflective</qex> faculties . . . thus
acquired a precocious and extraordinary development.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Addicted to introspective or meditative habits;
<as>as, a <ex>reflective</ex> person</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>Reflexive; reciprocal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*flect"ive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*flect"ive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Reflectiveness</xex> of manner.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. C.
Shairp.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reflector</ent>⟦br⟧
